Commentary.Commentary: We are back. Sri Lanka players now take the field. Followed by the opening pair of Pakistan, Abdullah Shafique and Imam-ul-Haq to take on the new ball. Asitha Fernando to start with the ball.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

The visitors were excellent with the ball. It was Naseem Shah and Shaheen Afridi who ran a havoc at the start. They picked up three and one wickets respectively. Abrar Ahmed then join them and ended with a four-fer. Pakistan bowlers have done their job and that too really well. The onus is now on the batters to put up a mammoth total and put the hosts under pressure. The conditions though are not that easy. The Lankans have struggled and so will the Pakistan batters. Will the Lankan bowlers get the early wickets? Or will Pakistan continue its dominance? We will find out soon. Join us in a bit for the Pakistan innings...

SESSION SUMMARY - 22.4 overs, 87 runs, and 6 wickets. That was certainly a poor display of batting from the Lankan side. They have been bowled out for 166 runs. The fifth-wicket partnership of 86 between Dhananjaya de Silva and Dinesh Chandimal was the only crucial partnership for them. The formar was dismissed by Abrar Ahmed while Chandimal fell on a short ball from Naseem Shah. Only four of the Lankan batters went into double digits, rest all were dismissed on a single digit. They will be certainly hoping for their bowlers to recover from this damage.

The home side will be upset with how things panned out in this session. Their made some wrong short selections and kept on losing wickets. They are currently reeling on 79-4 and Dinesh Chandimal and Dhananjaya de Silva will look to steady the sinking ship and build up a gritty stand for their side. Can they do it? Or will the visitors continue to dominate? To find out, do join us at 1.10 pm IST (7.40 am GMT) post lunch break.

SESSION SUMMARY - 26 overs, 79 runs, and 4 wickets. A session that was dominated by the visitors. They will be the happier side going into the break. The pitch certainly had something for the pacers and Shaheen Afridi and Naseem Shah made the most of it. They kept on picking wickets at regular intervals and kept on building the pressure on the Lankans. Naseem Shah picked up two wickets while Shaheen Afridi chipped in with one. They were excellent with their fielding as well with Shan Masood dismissing Nishan Madushka via a direct hit.

Sri Lanka had a long day with the ball, just two overs today but they toiled hard on Day 3 as Pakistan were unstoppable and resilient. Prabath Jayasuriya didn't got most of the home pitch this time as he ended with just two wickets. Asitha Fernando did got some reverse swing as he ended with three but apart form that it was a tiring outing for the Lankans. Now then, a huge task awaits. Sri Lanka were bowled out for 166 first time. They need more than that, a lot more actually to get a result.

Wow! That was quick! Rizwan reaches his fifty and Pakistan declare it. Just the two overs Sri Lanka had to come out to bowl. The lead is of 410 now and a huge task awaits for the Lankans. It was a batting exhibition from Pakistan. Apart from Imam-ul-Haq everyone has contributed. Abdullah Shafique was the start in the first phase of the innings as he scored a double ton and the baton was passed to Agha Salman who get his ton as well. Contributions from Shan Masood, Saud Shakeel and Mohammad Rizwan helped Pakistan get over 570.

Pakistan continue their dominance! Yet another solid session for them! The start was not the best as they lost Azam early. Sri Lanka bowled really well at the start, especially Prabath Jayasuriya who got some purchase out of the wicket but as the session went on, Abdullah Shafique and Saud Shakeel both started scoring at a decent rate. The bowling also was not great as the session progressed. Pakistan now lead over 100 and they will want to keep batting. Sri Lanka on the other hand, will hope for a few quick wickets after the break. Join us for the second session in a bit.

...Day 2, Session 1...

Sri Lanka needed an early wicket and Asitha Fernando provided them with the start they were after. He could've also gotten the better of Shan Masood if they would've reviewed an lbw decision which the umpire had turned down, and this could've helped them to shift the momentum on their side, but it was not to be. The bowlers were made to toil since then, and hardly put the batters under pressure. Eventually, Asitha Fernando picked his second wicket, by getting rid of one of the set-batter, who was left of the hook early on. Still, the Sri Lankan bowlers have their task cut out, and would hope to make a sharp comeback in the first session of Day 2.  So, will Pakistan continue their domination? Or will Sri Lanka be able to make early inroads in this game? We shall find out together. The first ball will be at 10 am IST (4.30 am GMT), but you can join us for the build-up. Cheers!

Undoubtedly, it has been Pakistan's day. They were on the money from the get go. After a delayed start to the match due to rain early on, the dark clouds did not interrupt the game even once, and all-in-all it was a good day for cricket. Pakistan took two session to bundle out the hosts for 166 runs, and now they end the first day on a high as they only trail by 21 runs with 2 wickets in hand. Shan Masood contributed with a well-made 50, but slipped out soon after. Later, Abdullah Shafique continued his good work alongwith his skipper. Abdullah Shafique was given out right at the brink of stumps, but he smartly took a review which forced the umpires to overturn their decision. In the end, one can say that the rub of the green was certainly not with Sri Lanka on Day 1.

The umpires comes together and are a bit concerned about the BAD LIGHT. They take the reading and asks the batters to walk off. So, it looks like that will be STUMPS. The session summary reads 28.3 overs 145 runs and 2 wickets. This is contrating to Sri Lanka's performance with the blade. Despite winning the toss, it is Pakistan that are certainly ahead in the game now.

Commentary.Commentary: Babar Azam is now presented with the trophy and now he celebrates along with his team! It has been a comprehensive win for Pakistan. That is it from this series. We hope you enjoyed our company. Until next time, goodbye and take care!

Babar Azam says he is very pleased to have won the series and the team was eager to do so. Adds the team was brilliant, everybody put on a show and he is very pleased. Credits the way Saud Shakeel, Agha Salman and Abdullah Shafique played. Ends by saying they are looking forward for the games coming their way.

Dimuth Karunaratne says they were poor with the bat and they gave away the wickets and it was difficult to come back into the game after that. Adds batters are getting starts but not converting it and it is opposite with the Pakistan batters. Mentions Pakistan won the crucial moments in the game and their batting was key. Admits they played far too many shots and they should have played a lot better.

Agha Salman, MAN OF THE MATCH, starts by saying, they were in trouble in the first innings of the first Test and they need a stand and it came between him and Saud Shakeel! States he does not mind where he bats, he just wants to play for Pakistan. Adds he is happy with his strike rate and he likes playing that way.

Abdullah Shafique, MAN OF THE MATCH, says it is a confidence booster as they have struggled in this version lately. Adds he is happy about his contribution. States he likes playing here and the team's win is the most important thing.
... TIME FOR PRESENTATION ...

They declared with a lead massive lead and yet again ensured Lanka do not cross the 200-run mark. The application from the Lankan batters was poor yet again. It was a combination of some poor shots and some good bowling but overall, Sri Lanka will be very disappointed with their performance in this series.

Right from Day 1, it was about Pakistan! They were asked to field first but they bundled Lanka out for a very low score. Abrar Ahmed and Naseem Shah were key sharing 7 wickets between them. In reply, Pakistan batted, batted and batted, they batted the hosts out of the game by scoring over 500. One centurion and one double centurion. There were contributions from others too but Abdullah Shafique, who scored a double ton and Agha Salman who got a ton were thhe highlights.

Yet another convincing performance from the visitors and they have recorded one of their biggest victories in Test cricket! Also, with this one, they have won the series 2-0. Nauman Ali and Naseem Shah were the stars for them on Day 5. Post this session, it was Nauman Ali who was brilliant and ended with a seven-fer whereas, after the break, it was Naseem Shah who ran through the tail. Outstanding.

An outstanding session for Pakistan and they are just the 4 wickets away from winning this! Nauman Ali was the star for them! He has all the six wickets so far. Some were good deliveries but most of them were gifted to him. The Lankan batters were trying to play their shots and in that process gifted their wickets. Lanka are a long, long way behind and they need a miracle even if they are to avoid an innings defeat. Pakistan on the other hand, will want to end this quickly after the break. Stay tuned.
A single as this is pushed towards deep cover. THAT WILL BE TEA!

A really good first session for the hosts.  Dimuth Karunaratne and Nishan Madushka laid a good foundation. The latter was a bit nervy as he was beaten quite a few times but gave his skipper a good hand to put a half century stand. However, Nishan Madushka was dismissed on the very first ball of Ali. The seamers got some swing but Sri Lanka negotiated well but it feels like the spinners will control the second session more as they are getting a good purchase. Nauman Ali will be key for Pakistan from here on. Stay tuned.
